<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 3:59AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...Enhanced Fire Danger Through Early Evening...
A dry air mass will settle into the southern Appalachians today
causing afternoon relative humidity to drop into the 20s across
much of east Tennessee, southwest Virginia, and Cherokee and Clay
counties of North Carolina. Winds will become northwesterly at 8
to 14 mph with gusts up to 20 mph possible, especially over the
ridge tops and mountains.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities
whether you may burn outdoors. Residents of the area are
discouraged from burning today...due to the increased potential
for fire growth and spread.</description>
